  "body": "Lodestar is downscoring more peers that usual reducing the total count of peers with score > 0\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-05-30 11-01-18](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/170918927-e6527aad-3104-4890-8971-5e9ad12a4989.png)\r\n\r\nThis affects the average mesh size of each topic, below target levels\r\n\r\n \r\n![Screenshot from 2022-05-30 11-01-48](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/170918995-727d1530-af81-41cd-94b7-cf9287e15176.png)\r\n\r\nThis creates more churn and inclusion events as Gossip tries to meet the target levels\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-05-30 11-17-31](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/170919038-91655fd9-3cf1-4d53-91e6-6e30cad3a63a.png)\r\n\r\nThe low scores seem to be caused mainly by p3b weights on beacon_attestation topics. \r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-05-30 11-41-44](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/170919088-8cec4d1e-b70a-4986-b8fc-78ca8c1bf990.png)\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @dapplion in https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/4074#issuecomment-1140694465_",
